<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>259298</id>
	<title>Proxy settings imported correctly but not enabled</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; rv:1.7.3) Gecko/20040913 Firefox/0.10
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; rv:1.7.3) Gecko/20040913 Firefox/0.10</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">When importing settings from Internet Explorer, the proxy information is
correctly imported, but the check box to use proxies is not selected.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.3">1 File -&gt; Import -&gt; Microsoft IE -&gt; Internet Options -&gt; Finish</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.4">2 Tools -&gt; Options -&gt; General -&gt; Connection Settings</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.5">3 Have to manually select "Automatic proxy configuration" even though the url</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.6">is correctly imported.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.7">Have to change from "Direct Connection to Internet".</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.8">4 Without manually changing it, connections time out</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Actual Results:  
With manual change, regained functionality.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">Expected Results:  
Detect that IE was using an automatic proxy and select that option in addition
to just importing the url.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="6">
			<sentence id="6.1">For a casual user trying to tranisition from IE, this will prevent the browser
from working on the first load, creating a really bad first impression.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
